title.22: Spider-Man/Doctor Strange: The Way to Dusty Death (1992)
title.37: The Amazing Spider-Man: Soul Of The Hunter (1992) #1

description.0: The Hulk, with the help of the Punisher, the Pantheon, and the police, avenge the death of Michael Berengetti!
description.2: Bullets! Explosions! Sharks! The Punisher and Shotgun close in on Frank's final target!
description.4: Heimdall - a traitor to Asgard? Thor certainly believes so!
description.6: Cyber, the mutant mentor of Hell's Belles, confronts X-Factor at a hotel in Virginia. Havok shows his true colors in battle, while Strong Guy finds himself in grave danger. Will the team be able to stop Cyber before his reign of terror continues?
description.8: The dark copy of Reed Richards has suceeded in taking his place, but can it fool Reed's wife, the Invisible Woman? Then, the Thing find himself locked in battle with a doppelganger of his own!
description.9: What is the cause of the madness that has swept the Morlock tunnels, infecting the subterranean mutants and driving them insane?
description.10: Wolverine takes Jubilee on a mission to stop a group of eco-terrorists, but the two mutants might need some extra help to get the job done!
description.11: A radical new look is needed for Wolverine to infiltrate a group of environmental extremists and rescue their hostage!
description.20: Frank Castle and Microchip take on the Praetorian Brotherhood!
description.24: Infinity War tie-in!  Can Moon Knight defeat his doppelganger sent by Magus in time to save Franklin Richards?
description.26: Spider-Man's 30th Anniversary special! Check out an anthology of stories chronicling the rise of everyone's favorite wall-crawler! J. Jonah Jameson reflects on his 'creation' of Spider-Man, while MJ recalls her intermingled history with Gwen Stacy. Plus, the Lizard attacks!
description.27: It's the Avengers vs the intergaltic pirates the Starjammers! When some of the Starjammers are looking to collect on a Kree bounty put out on the Black Knight, the two teams go head-to-head.
description.28: It's Captain America versus Wolverine! And Moonhunter is waiting to bury the loser! Find out who will win when the Shield of Liberty faces the sharpest claws there is!
description.32: Lilith has broken free of her imprisonment, and gathers whatever remaining ‘children' she can find to attack Ghost Rider and Johnny Blaze!
description.33: She-Hulk uses her scientific skills to figure out a way to contain Spragg once and for all!
description.35: Ghost Rider is confronted by the Caretaker who helps them escape Cypress Hill Cemetery to take on Lilith and her demonic visions!
description.38: It's Captain America versus the malevolent Moonhunter! When a bounty is placed on the wolf humanoid, Ferocia, Captain America and Wolverine seek to save her from those who wish to capture her!
description.49: The Finale of Timequake! What if the Watcher saves the Multiverse? Though under oath to never interfere, will Uatu break his vow to stop the Time-Keepers from erasing all other universes but their own? And what part to play does Immortus have in this multiversal conflagration?
description.53: Shocker runs afoul of Spider-Man, although the villain's amped up technology does give the wall-crawler a run for his money! Meanwhile, a mysterious couple arrives from Germany intent on changing Peter's life forever.
description.54: The search for John Jameson begins! Plus: A werewolf on the hunt! Don't miss this spooky issue, guest-starring Wolverine.
description.58: Doctor Doom wants something from Moon Knight and if he has to peel Marc Spector out of his new armor to get it, that's what he'll do.
description.64: A prisoner transfer goes horribly wrong - and Sabretooth is loose on the streets!
description.65: Spragg and the Hill People are out for revenge after being launched into outer space!
description.66: Spider-Man and Daredevil pull the plug on a surgeon who is selling organs on the black market.
description.67: Rachel Grey's mind is trapped in a coma, so Excalibur turns to the greatest master of the mind on Earth - Charles Xavier!
description.68: Joe Fixit is back in Vegas- and back with a vengeance!
description.70: Beat to a pulp and strapped to a car ready to explode, the Punisher needs some help. Enter: Shotgun!
description.72: Havoc is wreaked in Asgard when Karnilla attempts to wake Odin from his Odinsleep!
description.73: Mysterio places Spider-Man in a blockbuster illusion that plays out as the story of Peter Parker's life!
description.74: Introducing Hell's Belles! X-Factor must take down a terrorist cell comprised of female mutants. What do Hell's Belles want from X-Factor? And will the team be able to save a Belle-gone-good before her fellow teammates retaliate?
description.76: The Infinity War comes to the FF's doorstep! The sinister Magus has begun his assualt on Earth and its heroes, using evil doppelgangers to attack them one by one. His next target - Reed Richards, aka Mr. Fantastic!
description.77: To protect the Drake family, Iceman and Hiro battle the Cyburai!
description.78: It's an all-out melee for our group of heroes in Japan! Who will walk away unscathed, and who will be changed forever? Answers: no one, and everyone!
description.79: Wolverine must make the hardest decision of his life when Mariko is poisoned with blowfish toxins...
description.84: Betrayed by their friends and pursued by'everyone's favorite bounty hunter,'Han'and'Leia'try to escape from'Nar Shaddaa. Meanwhile, the'Rebels'in'combat'over the'planet'Calamari'receive aid from an unexpected source, and'Luke falls deeper into the grip of the'Dark Side!
description.91: Guest-starring Spider-Man! Daredevil urges the Wall-Crawler to pull a ruse on a surgeon who is harvesting her dates’ body parts.
description.92: A crisis of Jurassic proportions! Excalibur heads to the alternate world known as Earth-99476 - its Savage Land, to be precise!
description.93: Hulk battles the powerful Trauma in an attempt to save Atalanta! Does Hulk have what it takes to stand up to this new enemy? Meanwhile, Rick Jones is confronted with some shocking news about his mother...
description.95: The Punisher's cover is blown! Which means only one option - blow away all the bad guys!
description.96: Thor and Spider-Man reach an accord...and take off after Titania and the Absorbing Man!
description.98: Multiple Man and Quicksilver must take down a mutant music teacher gone rogue. But when Rhapsody uses her powers of mind manipulation, will the heroes fall under her musical spell? The first appearance of Rachel Argosy, the mutant known as Rhapsody!

1.text: Stark, in the War Machine armor, teams up with the Masters of Silence to take down Justin Hammer once and for all! It's a deadly battle on an isolated island against the combined threats of mercenaries, Mandroids, Hydra and the Hand!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #283)

3.text: Guest-starring the heroes of Excalibur! Spider-Man heads to London to follow up on a Sherlock-esque mystery involving Captain Britain.

19.text: Cyttorak captures Doctor Strange and Nova as his High Priest and Priestess on his journey to the source of Eternity’s defeat. Strange calls upon Juggernaut.

22.text: Welcome to the Death Dimension! Somewhere beyond time and space is a phantasmagoric landscape populated by demons, evil wizards and damsels in distress. A netherworld where the forces of darkness rule supreme. A nightmare realm where Spider-Man and Doctor Strange must wage a very personal battle, with the fate of the entire universe at stake. Welcome to the Death Dimension. No one gets out alive.

23.text: Kingpin is seeking to make Europe the new home of his crime-ridden empire. Punisher will have to continue past one of his henchmen first in order to reach the head honcho.

25.text: Nova, Namorita and Firestar try to liberate Vance from the convoy escorting him to prison!

29.text: Nomad and Captain America star in an Alaskan showdown! Why has Nomad gone rogue? And will Jack Monroe finally get the answers he’s looking for?

30.text: Cage in Colorado! Picking up a job for Troop, Cage and Micky travel to the American West to locate a missing guardian. A sinister state trooper is much more than he seems.

31.text: Infinity War tie-in. The Guardians must return to the 20th century to save fallen teammate Talon. Will advanced Inhuman medicine be the cure? Four Freedoms Plaza is destroyed. But why are the Inhumans blaming the Guardians?

32.text: Lilith has broken free of her imprisonment, and gathers whatever remaining ‘children' she can find to attack Ghost Rider and Johnny Blaze!

33.text: She-Hulk uses her scientific skills to figure out a way to contain Spragg once and for all!

35.text: Ghost Rider is confronted by the Caretaker who helps them escape Cypress Hill Cemetery to take on Lilith and her demonic visions!

36.text: Want to learn more about the armed-and-dangerous Nick Fury? In this issue, discover how he was recruited to the O.S.S.!

37.text: Although Kraven the Hunter is dead and buried, his memory still haunts Peter Parker more than the wall crawling hero will admit. Is it all in Peter's mind or is Kraven still hunting Spider-Man from the grave?

39.text: Frank Castle does like the 1980s and goes to a ski resort! However, this won't be your typical getaway...

41.text: After X-Force discovers Domino's treacherous ways, the team is hard-pressed to trust her again. In order to gain their trust back, Domino takes part in Cable's plan to bring Tolliver to justice.

42.text: Warlock and the revenge of the Beast!

43.text: The evil dopplegangers infiltration of the Marvel heroes has led to mistrust and infighting...and things get worse when a Gamma bomb is detonated!
The evil dopplegangers infiltration of the Marvel heroes has led to mistrust and infighting...and things get worse when a Gamma bomb is detonated!

44.text: The X-Men are in a twisted Wizard of Oz landscape…courtesy of Mojo!

45.text: Now freed from the Brood’s grasp, Ghost Rider teams with the X-Men to take down the Assassins’ Guild.

46.text: Who is killing the Changelings? Nick Fury is on a mission to find out for himself.

51.text: Galactus seizes his precious Eye from Doc. Agamotto is enraged by Galactus’ actions and fights him.

56.text: BIOHAZARD AGENDA PART 2 Deathlok reunites with his family! Michael returns to his wife Tracy only to be greeted with a cold reception from her relatives. What shocking news will Tracy Collins reveal? And will Deathlok be able to restore his relationship with his family?

59.text: Tai's determination to seize and harness the power of the Dragon's Breadth leads to an unlikely union between the New Warriors and the Folding Circle.

61.text: Dakota North’s been kidnapped by members of The Untouchables, and only Cage and Punisher have the intel to save her. But will Cage’s worst shakedown of Hardcore be enough?

62.text: At long last! The origin of the Guardians revealed! How did Vance, Charlie, Marty, and Yondu come to be galactic explorers and defenders? What happened at their first meeting? Everything you’ve wanted to know about the team’s backstory is in this issue!

64.text: A prisoner transfer goes horribly wrong - and Sabretooth is loose on the streets!

65.text: Spragg and the Hill People are out for revenge after being launched into outer space!

66.text: Spider-Man and Daredevil pull the plug on a surgeon who is selling organs on the black market.

69.text: This is it! The debut of the War Machine armor! And Iron Man's going to need all the firepower at his disposal to stop the armor-piercing weapons of the Masters of Silence, who are determined to make Stark pay! And behind it all? The devious Justin Hammer!  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #282)

71.text: INFINITY WAR crossover! A fearsome battle with the Demogoblin sends Spider-Man’s life spinning.

81.text: When Silver Surfer visits Titan, home world of Thanos, he learns the whereabouts of Galactus thanks to the Mentor. Surfer goes back to Earth, confronts Galactus, and learns Doctor Strange is trapped in a trance!

83.text: Excalibur faces off against the X-Men in this thrilling issue!

85.text: As Tolliver dispatches Deadpool to deal with Domino, Deadpool breaks into the X-Force's fortress and battles Shatterstar. Meanwhile, S.H.I.E.L.D makes a daring plan to capture Cable.

86.text: Omega captures Drax, Pop, Gamora, and Moondragon and plans on using their powers to kill their old for Warlock!

87.text: When evil dopplegangers of the Marvel heroes appear, it's all-out war!  Why has Magus unleashed them on an unsuspecting world? And is the heroes only hope...Thanos?!
When evil dopplegangers of the Marvel heroes appear, it's all-out war!  Why has Magus unleashed them on an unsuspecting world? And is the heroes only hope...Thanos?!

88.text: The Fantastic Four foray into the fray to fight the foes no single Spider-Friend could withstand!

89.text: The X-Men are surprised by a Brood attack in New Orleans! Ghost Rider guest-stars.

90.text: Now that the Silver Surfer has destroyed the Death Shrine, he has won the love of Princess Alaisa. The Princess is determined to show the Surfer that she is more than a mere mortal.

91.text: Guest-starring Spider-Man! Daredevil urges the Wall-Crawler to pull a ruse on a surgeon who is harvesting her dates’ body parts.

94.text: Tony Stark, despite being paralyzed, has been blamed for a nuclear-reactor meltdown in Japan - and the Japanese want revenge! When the armored ninjas of the Masters of Silence target Iron Man, can Stark complete the new War Machine armor in time?  (Originally published as IRON MAN (1992) #281)
